message.content: An Old English sheepdog is a large breed of dog that originated in England as a herding dog. It has a distinctive appearance with a shaggy coat that is typically white with gray markings. The coat is thick and woolly, providing good protection from the elements. The dog has a square-shaped body, with a broad head and droopy ears. Its eyes are usually blue or brown and are very expressive. The Old English sheepdog is friendly, loyal and playful, making it a popular family pet. They can often be found in dog shows and used as therapy dogs.
